Profile non-numeric atomic vectors.

profile_nonnumeric takes non-numeric atomic vectors and returns a data.frame containing important descriptive statistics.

profile_nonnumeric(.x)

Arguments

.x

a non-numeric atomic vector to be profiled.

Value

a data.frame containing important descriptive statistics.

Examples

# Example
profile(letters)
#>   .count_elements .count_uniques .percent_uniques .count_NULLs .percent_NULLs
#> 1              26             26                1            0              0
#>   .count_NAs .percent_NAs .count_zeroes .percent_zeros .mean_value .sd_value
#> 1          0            0             0              0          NA        NA
#>   .q0_value .q25_value .q50_value .q75_value .q100_value
#> 1         a         NA         NA         NA           z
#>                                                 .top_5_values
#> 1 (1) a [1]\n (1) b [1]\n (1) c [1]\n (1) d [1]\n (1) e [1]\n
#>                                              .bottom_5_values
#> 1 (1) z [1]\n (1) y [1]\n (1) x [1]\n (1) w [1]\n (1) v [1]\n
